# Designbook Agent Rules

## Dev Server Termination
Never use `send_command_input` with `Terminate: true` to stop dev servers (Storybook, Vite, Webpack).
They trap SIGTERM for graceful shutdown and will hang indefinitely.
Instead, kill via port: `lsof -ti:<PORT> | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null`

## Commands

### Linting
```bash
# Lint TypeScript (addon) — MUST pass before committing
npm run lint
# Auto-fix formatting
cd packages/storybook-addon-designbook && npx eslint --cache --fix .
# Lint CSS (integration)
npm run lint:css
npm run lint:css:fix
```

### Testing
```bash
# Run all tests (vitest) — MUST pass before committing
npm run test
# Run addon tests only
cd packages/storybook-addon-designbook && npx vitest run
```

### Development
```bash
npm run dev:integration:drupal   # Start Storybook (Drupal integration)
npm run dev:addon                # Build addon in watch mode
```

### Build
```bash
npm run build
```

## Code Style

- **Formatting**: Prettier via ESLint (`prettier/prettier`), 2-space indent, single quotes
- **TypeScript**: Strict, avoid `any` — use `Record<string, unknown>` or proper types
- **Imports**: ESM only (`import`/`export`), no `require()`

## Architecture

### Renderer (`src/renderer/`)
All rendering goes through `ScreenNodeRenderService`:
- `sdc-renderer.ts` — component nodes → SDC/Twig code
- `entity-renderer.ts` — entity nodes → JSONata resolution
- `presets/sdc.ts` — Pre-configured renderer set for Drupal/SDC

### Vite Plugin (`src/vite-plugin.ts`)
Transforms `.screen.yml` / `.section.yml` → CSF story modules via `ScreenNodeRenderService`.

### View Modes
`.jsonata` files in `designbook/view-modes/` — pattern: `{entity_type}.{bundle}.{view_mode}.jsonata`

## Before Committing — MANDATORY

**ALWAYS run these checks before every `git commit`. Do NOT skip.**

```bash
# 1. Lint (auto-fix first, then verify)
cd packages/storybook-addon-designbook && npx eslint --cache --fix . && cd ../..
npm run lint

# 2. Tests
cd packages/storybook-addon-designbook && npx vitest run && cd ../..
```

If either command fails, fix the issues before committing. Never commit with lint errors or failing tests.
